com.serena.dmclient.objects
Class RuleStateSelector

java.lang.Object
  com.serena.dmclient.objects.RuleStateSelector

public class RuleStateSelector
extends java.lang.Object

Encapsulates predefined Dimensions baseline template rule state selectors.

The following applies only when defining item baseline templates:

With the exception of a item baseline template that selects all item types, no more than one revision of an item will be selected for inclusion in a baseline. However, it is possible that more than one item of the selected type is present at the lifecycle state specified in the baseline template rule. In this case, the last edited item revision will be used. Use this class to specify the lifecycle state this item revision should be at.

The following applies only when defining request baseline templates:

Only EQS and SUP rule state selectors can be used in request baseline templates.

See Also:
BaselineTemplateRule.getLifecycleStatus()

Method Detail

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Returns a string object representing this RuleStateSelector's value.

If this object represents the "Specified State Only" selector, a string equal to "EQS" is returned.

If this object represents the "Specified State OR Most Progressed State" selector, a string equal to "SMP" is returned.

If this object represents the "Specified State OR next existing state Upward" selector, a string equal to "SUP" is returned.

If this object represents the "Latest from State" selector, a string equal to "LFS" is returned.

If this object represents the "Most Progressed State above specified state or specified state" selector, a string equal to "MPS" is returned.

If this object represents the "Specified Stage Only" selector, a string equal to "EQB" is returned.

If this object represents the "Specified Stage OR next existing stage UPward" selector, a string equal to "BUP" is returned.
